questions:
I'll be playing 20 Questions with you. I'll ask yes/no questions to figure out what you're thinking of, one question at a time.

Is the thing you're thinking of a physical object?

Question 19: Is this wooden storage object with open shelves used for storing or organizing office supplies or documents?
Question 20: Is this wooden storage object with open shelves used for storing or displaying plants?
final_guess:
a wooden shelf or shelving unit (like an open bookcase or display shelf) used for general storage purposes.

The answers have been somewhat contradictory - you confirmed it has shelves and is for storage, but ruled out most specific storage purposes (books, media, decorative items, small household items, electronics, office supplies, plants). Since it's a wooden storage item with open shelves found in living rooms but not primarily for any of the specific categories I asked about, a general-purpose shelving unit seems most likely.
